If you have to use a custom class. There are some irrelevant variables in your class and the logic is also incorrect. You may rewrite your class into something like this: &lt;sup&gt;(feel free to translate the variables/method names into your language)&lt;/sup&gt;

    class Stoper
    {
        public TimeSpan ElapsedTime { get; set; }

        private DateTime startDate;

        public void Start()
        {
            startDate = DateTime.Now;
        }

        public void Stop()
        {
            ElapsedTime = DateTime.Now - startDate;
        }
    }

Then, you can use it in the same way the `StopWatch` class is used above:

